quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  3,1,"Alif Lām Mīm."
  3,2,"Allah—there is no god but He, the Living, the All-Sustaining."
  3,3,"He bestowed upon you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>the Scripture from on high with the truth, confirming what preceded it. And He sent down the Torah and the Gospel"
  3,4,"previously, as guidance for mankind, and He sent down the Criterion. Indeed, for those who have denied Allah’s signs is a severe punishment, for Allah is Almighty, Capable of vengeance."
  3,5,"Indeed, nothing in the earth or in the heaven is hidden from Allah."
  3,6,"It is He Who designs you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>in the wombs as He wills. There is no god except He, the Almighty, the All-Wise."
  3,7,"It is He Who sent down upon you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>the Scripture. Some of its signs are explicit; they are the foundation{1}of the Scripture, while others are equivocal. So as for those whose hearts swerve, they follow whatever is equivocal of it, seeking tribulation and seeking its interpretation. But none knows its interpretation except Allah. Thus, those firmly rooted in knowledge say, “We have attained faith in it; all is from our Lord.” But none constantly remembers except those with understanding.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘the mother of the Scripture’.
  3,8,"“Our Lord, do not cause our hearts to swerve after You have guided us, and bestow upon us mercy from You; indeed, You are the Superb Bestower."
  3,9,"“Our Lord, You will certainly gather mankind for a day about which there is no doubt.” Indeed, Allah{1}never breaks a promise.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 2nd person to 3rd person.
